![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/1779ea7a-fdb3-4e87-a18d-52ae8a9e38bd/Screenshot_20240821_180100.jpg?format=original)

Will Ospreay: YOU'RE JUST MAD BECAUSE THESE PEOPLE DON'T LOVE YOU

MJF: THESE PEOPLE LOVED ME BEFORE YOU SHOWED UP

Incredible segment between MJF and Will Ospreay that started with Ospreay talking about how he's saving AEW from the kind of "entertainment" MJF brings.

MJF says Ospreay can't beat him because he's too afraid to use the only move that can do it.

Ospreay keeps poking and prodding MJF. Making fun of the Adam Cole storyline that went sideways and saying Tony Khan needed Ospreay to have a good match at All In last year because the main event was trash.

Eventually the truth slips out and MJF reveals he hates Ospreay because Ospreay is taking his spot in the fan's Heart.

MJF starts talking about Will Ospreay's adopted son, saying that after the conversation MJF had with Ospreay's wife. MJF had a feeling her next child won't be Will Ospreay's either.

Ospreay asks Shiavonne to ask Tony Khan how much will he be fined if he attacks MJF. Tony says $127k. Ospreay says it's worth it and attacks.

Security breaks them upong enough for MJF to get the ring out and take Ospreay down. MJF attempts a Tiger Driver of his own but security breaks it up.

